channel.title: Warrior Cats FM Signups [15/15]
channel.description:
https://img00.deviantart.net/509d/i/2012/231/0/7/warrior_cats_final_battle_by_cmoffitt1-d5boabt.png Photo is available at https://cmoffitt1.deviantart.com/art/Warrior-Cats-Final-Battle-321939785. # Warrior Cats FM - Hosted by @thepigeonnyc. Co-hosted and alt modded by @Arete. Reviewed by @orangeandblack5. Flavor written by @thedovenyc. # [color="red"]Warning, this OP and the game's flavor may contain minor spoilers to some books, particularly The Last Hope[/color] # Rules: 1. Follow the Global Forum Rules and the [Forum Mafia Rules](https://fol-archive.netlify.app/t/official-forum-mafia-and-forum-of-lies-rules/78926). # Gameplay: * Phases are 48/24 * Feedback is the same as FoL. * Cuddles are plurality and majority. Please ping me upon voting. * Votes are not locked in CuLo (cuddle-or-lose) or MuLo (miscuddle-and-lose). * In the case of a tie, the cuddle is randed between the people who have been voted most. * [color="forestgreen"]ThunderClan[/color] Vanilla cats do not know which Vanilla they are, they simply get the Vanilla PM shown below. * The [color="navy"]Dark Forest[/color] have a factional kill that is assigned and cannot be used alongside other abilities. It is usable by [color="navy"]Darkstripe[/color] once the other members are dead or if he joins the Dark Forest chat. Otherwise, he cannot use it. * The uninformed majority is [color="forestgreen"] ThunderClan[/color] and the informed minority is the [color="navy"]Dark Forest[/color]. * The win condition of [color="forestgreen"] ThunderClan [/color] is to kill the members of the [color="navy"] Dark Forest [/color]. * The win condition of the [color="navy"] Dark Forest [/color] is to gain parity with [color="forestgreen"]ThunderClan[/color].
[details="Roles (One of each will roll)"] > # [color=”forestgreen”] Squirrelflight [/color] > [color=”forestgreen”] **ThunderClan Neighborizer (in neighborhood)** [/color] > Night ability: Talks a Lot: Add or remove your target to/from a neighborhood chat that you are a part of. This chat lasts until you die and can be used at any time. Unlimited uses. > # [color=”forestgreen”] Leafpool [/color] > [color=”forestgreen”] **ThunderClan Jailkeeper** [/color] > Night ability: Bring to Medicine Den: Heal and roleblock your target tonight. 3 uses, however you cannot target the same person multiple times. > # [color=”forestgreen”] Jayfeather [/color] > [color=”forestgreen”] **ThunderClan Parity Cop** [/color] > Night ability: Read Mind: See if your target is the same alignment as your last. Unlimited uses. > # [color=”forestgreen”] Daisy [/color] > [color=”forestgreen”] **ThunderClan Vanilla** [/color] > You take care of kits at night, so you have no abilities. You are just another queen, so you don't know your character. > # [color="forestgreen"] Ferncloud [/color] > [color="forestgreen"] **ThunderClan Vanilla** [/color] > You also take care of kits at night, so you have no abilities. You are *yet another queen*, so you don't know your character. > # [color=”forestgreen”] Birchfall [/color] > [color=”forestgreen”] **ThunderClan Vanilla** [/color] > You train in the Dark Forest (don’t question the alignment) at night, so you have no abilities. You were just thrown into a list of cats who trained in the Dark Forest, so you don't know your character. > # [color=”forestgreen”] Purdy [/color] > [color=”forestgreen”] **ThunderClan Vanilla** [/color] > You stay in the elders’ den telling stories, so you have no abilities. You have blended in with the elders, so you do not know your character. > # [color=”forestgreen”] Thornclaw [/color] > [color=”forestgreen”] **ThunderClan Vanilla** [/color] > You go on patrols at night, so you have no abilities, and have forgotten your character from all that patrolling. > # [color="forestgreen"]Brackenfur[/color] > [color="forestgreen"] **ThunderClan Vanilla** [/color] > You are considered a boring character. As such, you have no abilities, and you don't know your character. > # [color="forestgreen"] Cinderheart [/color] > [color="forestgreen"] **ThunderClan Vanilla** [/color] > Since Cinderpelt just left your body, you don't have any abilities and you don't know your character. > # [color="forestgreen"] Lionblaze [/color] > [color="forestgreen"] **ThunderClan Vanilla** [/color] > The parts of the books where you're POV are so boring that you don't have any abilities and even you don't know your character. > # [color=”navy”] Tigerstar [/color] > [color=”navy”] **Dark Forest Godfather** [/color] > Passive: Former Deputy: You will appear as the same alignment as [color="forestgreen"]ThunderClan[/color] cats to [color="forestgreen"]Jayfeather[/color] > # [color="navy"] Brokenstar [/color] > [color="navy"] **Dark Forest Roleblocker** [/color] > Night ability: Distract: Stop your target from using abilities tonight. You cannot be roleblocked while using this ability. 3 uses. > # [color=”navy”] Mapleshade [/color] > [color=”navy”] **Dark Forest Goon** [/color] > You're too busy plotting your revenge to do anything but kill people. > # [color=”navy”] Darkstripe [/color] > [color=”navy”] **Dark Forest Traitor/Double Parity Cop** [/color] > Passive: Lost in the Dark Forest: The other members of the [color="navy"] Dark Forest [/color] do not know who you are and you do not know who they are, nor do you talk with them. > Night ability: Look for Tigerstar: Check if two people are of the same alignment. If they are the same, you will learn their alignment. If they are both members of the [color="navy"] Dark Forest [/color], then you will join their chat. You may target yourself when there is only one other member left, and this ability is disabled when you are the only member left. Unlimited uses. [/details] [details="Vanilla PM"] > # [color="forestgreen"] ThunderClan Vanilla [/color] > You have no abilities and you don't know your character. [/details] # Players: 1. sulit 1. Arctic 1. GGhana 1. Marshal 1. Aelin 1. Emilia 1. Leafia 1. SamCrow 1. min 1. EliThePsycho 1. Wazza 1. PokemonKidRyan 1. Marluxion 1. clonedcheese 1. Stealthbomber16 # Backups: 1. Warrior Catsuh 1. Whysper 1. WindwardAway 1. Nightingale 1. Amelia 1. Intensify # Spectators (informed and uninformed are allowed): 1. DatBird (undecided) 1. Mistyx (informed) 1. Chloe (uninformed) 1. Mercenary (informed) 1. Frostwolf103 (informed) 1. thedovenyc (informed) 1. astand (informed) 1. MaximusPrime (informed) # We need VC bots, preferably ones that are also informed specs so they can do flips in case of a hammer when the hosts are asleep.
